Samsung launched its Galaxy Tab S7 and S7+ last month, which the company describes as offering “the power of a PC, the flexibility of a tablet, and the connectivity of a smartphone”. The South African pricing for two versions of these tablets is now available on Samsung’s website, and is as follows: Pricing for other versions of these tablets is not yet available. Samsung claims that these devices’ displays are the most advanced ever used on a tablet. The Tab S7 has an 11-inch 2,560 x 1,600 LCD screen while the Tab S7+ has a 12.4-inch 2,800 x 1,752 Super AMOLED display. Both feature a 120Hz variable refresh rate. These tablets use the powerful Qualcomm Snapdragon 865+ processor and are available with up to 8GB RAM and 512GB storage. They also boast impressive batteries – 8,000mAh and 10,090mAh for the Tab S7 and Tab S7+ respectively – and offer support for 45W fast charging. The Galaxy Tab S7 and Tab S7+ also offer impressive camera systems, with a 13MP + 5MP dual rear camera system powered by software-driven features like Night Hyperlapse, Single Take, and Front and Back Conversion. Both tablets also have an 8MP front camera for high-quality selfies. The Tab S7 range also comes with the new S Pen, which Samsung said offers “ultra-low latency” and its “biggest leap in responsiveness”. These tablets come in three colours – Mystic Black, Mystic Silver, and Mystic Bronze. Specifications and images of the Samsung Galaxy Tab S7 and S7+ can be viewed below. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-362822" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Galaxy-Tab-S7-559x430.jpg" alt="" width="559" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Galaxy-Tab-S7-559x430.jpg 559w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Galaxy-Tab-S7-520x400.jpg 520w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Galaxy-Tab-S7.jpg 650w" sizes="(max-width: 559px) 85vw, 559px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-